# Backend (Go) conventions

- Module is `github.com/madmmas/temflowral/backend`, Go 1.25.7. Follow whatever
  `go.mod`'s toolchain directive says if it's changed since.
- HTTP request/response types come from the OpenAPI codegen output, not
  hand-written structs — see the generated-code directory's "DO NOT EDIT"
  header. If a type you need doesn't exist, the fix is adding it to
  `api/openapi.yaml` and regenerating, not writing a parallel struct.
- Temporal workflows must stay deterministic: no direct time.Now(), no raw
  goroutines, no random values, no network calls inside workflow code — those
  belong in activities. If you're not sure whether something belongs in a
  workflow or an activity, it almost certainly belongs in an activity.
- The graph → workflow translator is the core piece: it walks the `Graph`
  schema (nodes + edges) and dispatches to one Temporal activity per node
  type. New node types should mean a new activity implementation, not changes
  to the translator's control flow, unless the node introduces a genuinely new
  execution pattern (e.g. branching, parallelism).
- Activities that make outbound HTTP calls (the HTTP node) must validate
  target URLs before requesting — no SSRF via user-supplied config. This is
  called out in `SECURITY.md`; don't defer it to a follow-up PR.
- Run `golangci-lint run` before considering a change done — CI enforces it
  once `.golangci.yml` exists (`ISSUES.md` #20).
- Table-driven tests, `go test -race` — matches the Makefile's `test` target.
